 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.2.1","title":"robot-redesign/sqlite: design runtime tables and migration plan","description":"Design the SQLite schema that will hold runtime projections, source health, persistent attention events, incidents, and output watermarks. This task exists to make the persistent layer intentional rather than letting tables accrete around the first implementation that happens to work.","design":"The schema should separate durable source-of-truth state from derived robot-facing runtime state. It should describe table purposes, keys, indexes, retention boundaries, and the relationship between projection rows, source_health rows, attention events, incidents, and watermark/baseline tables.\\n\\nIt should also explain how migrations will be introduced safely into ntm's existing SQLite state store without pretending the new runtime data are equivalent to tmux truth.","acceptance_criteria":"Produce a concrete migration-ready table design with clear ownership for runtime_sessions, runtime_agents, runtime_work, runtime_coordination, runtime_quota, source_health, attention_events, incidents, and output_watermarks or equivalent structures.\\n\\nThe result must be explicit enough for store APIs and tests to proceed without re-litigating the data model.","notes":"Be conservative about schema complexity, but not simplistic. The goal is a durable projection substrate that can survive restart, replay, and parity work without needing a second database later.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:20.958522931Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T03:31:51.180732081Z","closed_at":"2026-03-22T03:31:51.179398123Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["projection","robot-redesign","sqlite"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:49.626506573Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:50.091006844Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:20.958522931Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":323,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"Future self: this is where the SQLite-only constraint gets turned into a real architecture instead of a slogan.","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:21Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.2.2","title":"robot-redesign/sqlite: implement store APIs and migration plumbing for runtime state","description":"Implement the store and migration plumbing needed to read and write the new runtime projection tables. This task exists so later builders and surfaces talk to typed storage APIs instead of writing SQL ad hoc throughout the codebase.","design":"The store layer should make projection writes, source-health updates, watermark persistence, incident persistence, and journal appends feel like first-class ntm operations. It should also enforce transactional boundaries that let projection recompute and event publication happen coherently.\\n\\nThe design should avoid leaking SQL details into unrelated robot packages.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when ntm has typed store methods and migrations for the new runtime state, and downstream tasks can persist and query projections without inventing their own schema access patterns.","notes":"A good outcome here reduces future drift and makes restart-safe behavior testable. A bad outcome spreads SQL around the robot and server packages and recreates today's duplication in a different form.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:22.197797158Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T16:41:58.908384757Z","closed_at":"2026-03-22T16:41:58.907801316Z","close_reason":"Verified implemented in runtime_store.go (1956 lines) + 007_runtime.sql migration. Store APIs: Session (Upsert/Get/Delete), Agent (Upsert/GetBySession/Delete), Work (Upsert/Get/List), Coordination (Upsert/Get/List), Quota (Upsert/Get/List), SourceHealth (Upsert/Get/GetDegraded), AttentionEvent (Append/GetSince/ReplayWindow), Incident (Create/Get/List/UpdateStatus), Watermark (Get/Set), Audit (Record/History/Trace). Both Store and Tx transaction variants. Full projection persistence layer with typed APIs.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["robot-redesign","sqlite","store"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:22.197797158Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:34.737403386Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.2.3","title":"robot-redesign/sqlite: build projection recompute/orchestration pipeline","description":"Build the orchestration path that takes normalized adapter outputs and writes a coherent runtime projection into SQLite. This task exists because the projection model only helps if ntm has one disciplined place where derived state is assembled and committed.","design":"The projection pipeline should define when recomputation happens, what counts as a full versus partial refresh, how related sections are committed transactionally, and how downstream consumers find a coherent latest view.\\n\\nThis is also the task that should decide whether some sections are materialized eagerly, lazily, or on-demand, provided the external contract remains crisp.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when ntm can build and persist a coherent runtime projection from normalized inputs, with clear recompute semantics and atomic visibility for consumers.","notes":"The builder should make later surfaces thinner, not more magical. If surface code still has to reconstruct core relationships, this task is incomplete.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:23.067786075Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T19:55:02.612813435Z","closed_at":"2026-03-22T19:55:02.612333676Z","close_reason":"Implemented normalized projection refresh/orchestration with transactional persistence for runtime_work, runtime_coordination, runtime_quota, source_health, runtime_sessions, and runtime_agents; verified with focused robot tests and targeted compile probes.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["projection","robot-redesign","sqlite"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:23.067786075Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:35.142219542Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:35.564109480Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-j9jo3.2.4","title":"robot-redesign/sqlite: define retention, pruning, and read/write amplification guardrails","description":"Define the retention, pruning, update-frequency, and read-path cost rules that keep the SQLite runtime layer healthy under continuous robot and server use. This task exists to ensure the redesign stays operationally cheap rather than quietly turning the state DB into a churny log sink or a slow query bottleneck.","design":"The task should address which runtime sections are snapshots versus append-only journals, how long attention events and incidents are retained, how watermarks are compacted, how projection recompute avoids rewriting everything on every poll, and what indexing or query-shape guardrails keep frequent summary and replay reads efficient.\n\nThe goal is not premature micro-optimization; it is preventing obvious write amplification, pathological read fanout, and unbounded growth.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when future implementers have explicit rules for pruning, bounded retention, update cadence, and read-path expectations, and when the SQLite layer has a documented stance on avoiding unnecessary rewrites and expensive routine queries.","notes":"Guardrails belong in the design, not as an afterthought discovered after the DB has already become noisy or slow under realistic operator polling.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":150,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:23.914567473Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-21T23:56:01.285241164Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["retention","robot-redesign","sqlite"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:23.914567473Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:35.977863283Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:36.409717511Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-j9jo3.2.4","title":"robot-redesign/sqlite: define retention, pruning, and read/write amplification guardrails","description":"Define the retention, pruning, update-frequency, and read-path cost rules that keep the SQLite runtime layer healthy under continuous robot and server use. This task exists to ensure the redesign stays operationally cheap rather than quietly turning the state DB into a churny log sink or a slow query bottleneck.","design":"The task should address which runtime sections are snapshots versus append-only journals, how long attention events and incidents are retained, how watermarks are compacted, how projection recompute avoids rewriting everything on every poll, and what indexing or query-shape guardrails keep frequent summary and replay reads efficient.\n\nThe goal is not premature micro-optimization; it is preventing obvious write amplification, pathological read fanout, and unbounded growth.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when future implementers have explicit rules for pruning, bounded retention, update cadence, and read-path expectations, and when the SQLite layer has a documented stance on avoiding unnecessary rewrites and expensive routine queries.","notes":"Guardrails belong in the design, not as an afterthought discovered after the DB has already become noisy or slow under realistic operator polling.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":150,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:23.914567473Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T02:50:17.958455668Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T02:50:17.957997150Z","close_reason":"Completed: codified runtime retention and pruning guardrails with RunGC(DefaultRuntimeGCConfig()), added bounded stale snapshot/source-health cleanup, documented the operational cadence/read-path rules, and made runtime_quota usage percentages explicit via used_pct_known plus used_pct_source.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["retention","robot-redesign","sqlite"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:23.914567473Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:35.977863283Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:36.409717511Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.2.5","title":"robot-redesign/sqlite: persist audit trail, actor attribution, and decision-history primitives","description":"Persist the audit primitives that let ntm reconstruct who changed what, when, and why across operator overrides, actuation loops, incident lifecycle changes, and disclosure-control decisions.","design":"The implementation should extend the SQLite runtime layer with a bounded, queryable audit trail keyed strongly enough to join with stable entity references, request IDs, incident fingerprints, and disclosure metadata. It should decide what gets persisted as full audit events versus compact summaries, how actor identifiers and origin classes are stored, how retention and pruning behave, how sensitive content is excluded or transformed inside the audit trail, and how store APIs make audit writes a normal part of attention-state changes, actuation outcomes, incident transitions, and redaction or disclosure decisions rather than an optional afterthought. This work should preserve trust and replay utility without creating an unbounded append-only swamp.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when ntm has typed SQLite primitives and retention-aware persistence for actor-attributed audit events and decision history, and downstream tasks can attach trustworthy audit records to operator overrides, actuation loops, incident changes, replay flows, and disclosure-control behavior without inventing their own side logs.","notes":"A useful audit trail is concise, queryable, and correlated. If it is so vague that it cannot answer who changed this and why, or so noisy that nobody will consult it, this task is incomplete.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-22T01:56:56.313037895Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T16:41:25.512571411Z","closed_at":"2026-03-22T16:41:25.512099107Z","close_reason":"Verified implemented. AuditEvent struct (runtime_schema.go:467-506) has full actor attribution (ActorType, ActorID, ActorOrigin), request correlation (RequestID, CorrelationID), event classification (Category, EventType, Severity), entity tracking (EntityType, EntityID), state changes (PreviousState, NewState, ChangeSummary), decision context (Reason, Evidence, DisclosureState), retention (RetentionClass, ExpiresAt). Store APIs: RecordAuditEvent, GetActorActivity, GetAuditHistory, GetRequestTrace, GCExpiredAuditEvents. AuditActor for actor correlation. Full audit trail implementation.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","robot-redesign","sqlite"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:56:56.313037895Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.3","title":"robot-redesign/adapters: normalize live sources into shared projections","description":"Build the source adapters that translate tmux state, process telemetry, beads/bv, Agent Mail, conflicts, handoff data, quota, alerts, and health signals into the canonical projection model. This epic exists because the shared projection layer only helps if all major robot-relevant inputs are normalized consistently.","design":"Adapters should hide source-specific weirdness and emit section-shaped data plus freshness/degraded metadata. They should not leak the old command-local assembly model upward.\\n\\nThe intent is to make later surfaces project the same underlying model regardless of whether they are rendered as JSON, TOON, markdown, terse summaries, REST payloads, or dashboard sections.","acceptance_criteria":"This epic is complete when the projection builder can consume normalized adapter outputs for all major robot-relevant domains and populate source_health deterministically.","notes":"Adapters are where we keep ntm tmux-first: tmux and session reality still drive the system, but every consumer sees that reality through a stable normalized shape.","status":"open","priority":4,"issue_type":"epic","estimated_minutes":300,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:06.496610791Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:20.384280320Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["adapters","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:06.496610791Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":315,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3","author":"ubuntu","text":"Future self: adapter code should absorb source idiosyncrasies so the rest of the system does not have to memorize how each upstream tool misbehaves.","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:07Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.3.1","title":"robot-redesign/adapters: build tmux/session/agent/process normalization adapter","description":"Normalize tmux session, pane, agent, process, and output-activity data into the canonical projection shape. This task exists because tmux is still the core source of truth for ntm, but consumers should no longer have to understand tmux's raw quirks directly.","design":"The adapter should unify pane/session inspection, process telemetry, activity signals, context telemetry, and agent-type detection into one stable shape. It should also define how raw pane identifiers, output timestamps, and process-derived fields map into runtime_sessions and runtime_agents.\\n\\nThis task should explicitly preserve ntm's tmux-first nature while insulating the rest of the robot stack from tmux-specific mechanics.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when tmux-derived runtime session and agent data can be produced in the canonical projection shape, with enough fidelity to drive snapshot, status, and attention surfaces.","notes":"If later surfaces still reach directly into tmux packages for core state assembly, this adapter task has not gone far enough.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:24.771141458Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T16:40:52.001704751Z","closed_at":"2026-03-22T16:40:52.001243104Z","close_reason":"Verified implemented in tmux_adapter.go (references bd-j9jo3.3.1 in header). TmuxAdapter normalizes tmux data to RuntimeSession/RuntimeAgent. Key methods: NormalizeSession(tmux.Session→RuntimeSession, line 84), NormalizeSessions (line 149), NormalizeAgent(Agent→RuntimeAgent, line 164), NormalizeAgents (line 214). Classifies agent state, maps pane identifiers, handles output timestamps and process fields. Acceptance criteria met: tmux-derived data in canonical projection shape.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["adapters","robot-redesign","tmux"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:50.596751190Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:24.771141458Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":324,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"This adapter is the spine of the redesign. If it stays ad hoc, everything above it will stay ad hoc too.","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:25Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.3.2","title":"robot-redesign/adapters: build work and coordination normalization adapter","description":"Normalize work and coordination signals such as beads/bv state, Agent Mail unread/backlog state, file conflicts, reservation conflicts, and handoff context into shared projection sections. This task exists because operator pain often comes from coordination state rather than from tmux state alone.","design":"The adapter should produce stable work and coordination sections that can answer questions like: what is ready, what is blocked, who has unread mail, where are reservation conflicts, what is the current handoff summary, and which coordination problems deserve attention.\\n\\nThe implementation should hide the peculiarities of each source tool so later surfaces can reason about coordination with one vocabulary.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when work and coordination sections can be populated from beads/bv, Agent Mail, tracker/conflict data, and handoff data without leaking each tool's bespoke output model upward.","notes":"This adapter is where the redesign becomes more agent-intuitive than today's scattered bridge commands.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:26.022106327Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T16:40:04.285322394Z","closed_at":"2026-03-22T16:40:04.284838085Z","close_reason":"Verified implemented in work_coordination.go. WorkSection (lines 28-62) normalizes beads/bv with Ready/Blocked/InProgress/Summary/Triage. CoordinationSection (lines 91-140) normalizes: MailSummary (Agent Mail unread/backlog), ReservationsSummary (file reservation pressure), HandoffSummary (handoff context). Adapter methods: summarizeMail, summarizeReservations, summarizeHandoff, collectCoordinationProblems. All acceptance criteria met: beads/bv, Agent Mail, tracker/conflict data, handoff data unified under one vocabulary.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["adapters","coordination","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:51.052836664Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:26.022106327Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.3.3","title":"robot-redesign/adapters: build system, quota, alert, and health normalization adapter","description":"Normalize non-tmux operational signals such as quota pressure, health checks, alerts, and system-level warnings into shared projection sections. This task exists because operator decisions require a coherent operational picture, not just pane state plus occasional bespoke warnings.","design":"The adapter should define how health summaries, rate-limit signals, quota warnings, crash/restart state, and system degradation are represented in stable sections and reason codes.\\n\\nIt should also ensure those signals can later promote into incidents instead of remaining forever as disconnected ephemeral warnings.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when global operational signals can be surfaced in the projection model with stable section names and reason-code-friendly data.","notes":"If a future consumer has to parse free-form alert text to understand quota or health state, this adapter task has failed.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:26.913850553Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T03:50:32.551067371Z","closed_at":"2026-03-22T03:50:32.549956130Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["adapters","health","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:51.516426791Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:26.913850553Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.3.4","title":"robot-redesign/adapters: compute source_health, freshness, and degraded feature state","description":"Compute source_health and degraded-feature information from all major adapters so every later surface can explain what is fresh, stale, partial, or unavailable. This task exists because freshness semantics must be produced systematically, not improvised by each renderer.","design":"The implementation should take adapter outputs plus failure states and emit section-level freshness and degradation metadata according to the contract defined earlier. It should decide how partial refreshes are represented, how source outages affect downstream sections, and how degraded features are advertised without drowning the response in noise.\\n\\nThis task is the bridge between adapter mechanics and trustworthy operator-facing semantics.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when runtime projections carry deterministic source_health and degraded feature state for all major sections and when later surfaces can reuse that data verbatim.","notes":"A surface should not have to decide on its own whether data are fresh or degraded. That decision belongs here.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":150,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:27.816413037Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T18:38:30.637501178Z","closed_at":"2026-03-22T18:38:30.637008095Z","close_reason":"Implemented in normalize.go: ComputeSourceHealth() for deterministic freshness/degradation from adapter results, ComputeDegradedFeatures() for feature impact mapping. SignalAggregator.Collect() now auto-computes source health. 7 tests added and passing.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["adapters","freshness","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:51.988102289Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},