-{"id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","title":"robot-redesign/adapters: implement redaction, safe previews, and disclosure metadata across normalized sources","description":"Implement the source-side and projection-side redaction path that lets ntm expose richer robot data without leaking secrets or sensitive text into live surfaces, durable projections, or replay artifacts.","design":"The implementation should introduce a disciplined disclosure-control layer in the normalization pipeline. It should decide where text and structured payloads are classified and sanitized before persistence or projection, how pane tails, mail snippets, diagnostic evidence, actuation arguments or outcomes, and replay snapshots produce safe previews instead of raw sensitive blobs, and how disclosure metadata such as redaction markers, rule versions, hashed evidence handles, and counts of hidden material are carried into the shared model. It should also decide whether and how ntm keeps a lightweight redaction audit trail in SQLite so diagnostics, docs, and tests can verify that sensitive material was transformed rather than silently dropped. This work should preserve operator usefulness: evidence should remain explainable and correlatable even when the raw content is hidden.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when normalized robot-visible source data can flow through ntm with deterministic redaction or disclosure-control behavior, safe previews where appropriate, explicit machine-readable markers for hidden or transformed content, and enough auditability that replay, diagnostics, and validation can prove the system did the safe thing rather than merely omitting data.","notes":"If secrets can still slip from tmux output, mail content, diagnostic evidence, or replay artifacts into robot surfaces without an explicit and testable disclosure decision, this task is incomplete.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-22T01:34:08.686306044Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T23:36:25.631419881Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["adapters","robot-redesign","sensitivity"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.14","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:22.431265216Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:23.265639252Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:24.082665161Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:24.904859723Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:34:08.686306044Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:25.731984289Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:26.546974345Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:27.366439404Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","title":"robot-redesign/adapters: implement redaction, safe previews, and disclosure metadata across normalized sources","description":"Implement the source-side and projection-side redaction path that lets ntm expose richer robot data without leaking secrets or sensitive text into live surfaces, durable projections, or replay artifacts.","design":"The implementation should introduce a disciplined disclosure-control layer in the normalization pipeline. It should decide where text and structured payloads are classified and sanitized before persistence or projection, how pane tails, mail snippets, diagnostic evidence, actuation arguments or outcomes, and replay snapshots produce safe previews instead of raw sensitive blobs, and how disclosure metadata such as redaction markers, rule versions, hashed evidence handles, and counts of hidden material are carried into the shared model. It should also decide whether and how ntm keeps a lightweight redaction audit trail in SQLite so diagnostics, docs, and tests can verify that sensitive material was transformed rather than silently dropped. This work should preserve operator usefulness: evidence should remain explainable and correlatable even when the raw content is hidden.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when normalized robot-visible source data can flow through ntm with deterministic redaction or disclosure-control behavior, safe previews where appropriate, explicit machine-readable markers for hidden or transformed content, and enough auditability that replay, diagnostics, and validation can prove the system did the safe thing rather than merely omitting data.","notes":"If secrets can still slip from tmux output, mail content, diagnostic evidence, or replay artifacts into robot surfaces without an explicit and testable disclosure decision, this task is incomplete.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-22T01:34:08.686306044Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T02:30:37.778018210Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T02:30:37.777528844Z","close_reason":"Completed after follow-up fix: persisted sanitized handoff summary plus disclosure metadata in runtime_handoff, surfaced it through projection-backed status, and added runtime/status persistence coverage.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["adapters","robot-redesign","sensitivity"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.14","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:22.431265216Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:23.265639252Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:24.082665161Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:24.904859723Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:34:08.686306044Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:25.731984289Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:26.546974345Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:27.366439404Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":362,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","author":"ubuntu","text":"Reopened: Reopened after fresh review: handoff disclosure metadata is