 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.4","title":"robot-redesign/attention: persistent journal, replay, and cursor semantics","description":"Persist the attention journal and related output/activity watermarks so ntm's operator loop survives process restarts and exposes replay-safe, cursor-safe deltas across CLI and server transports. This epic exists because the attention loop is already the best direction in ntm, but it still needs durable mechanics to become the true center of the robot interface.","design":"The intended outcome is a durable event stream with stable cursor semantics, bounded retention, deterministic replay, explicit resync behavior, and enough persisted output/activity context to compute deltas even after ntm restarts.\\n\\nThis epic also owns transport parity: replay semantics should not diverge between CLI JSON, REST, SSE, and WebSocket consumers.","acceptance_criteria":"This epic is complete when events, digest, and attention can operate over durable journal state instead of volatile in-memory-only assumptions.","notes":"The attention feed should become more central, not more magical. It remains a sensing and triage surface, not a hidden planner.","status":"open","priority":4,"issue_type":"epic","estimated_minutes":300,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:07.747504415Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T00:10:20.457426809Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["attention","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:07.747504415Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":316,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Future self: the operator loop is the product. Treat any cursor ambiguity, replay drift, or restart breakage as a first-order defect.","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:08Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.4.1","title":"robot-redesign/attention: implement SQLite-backed attention event store and cursor model","description":"Implement the durable event store and cursor model that back ntm's replay-safe attention loop. This task exists because a central product promise of the redesign is that attention, events, and digest survive process restarts and expose stable delta semantics.","design":"The design should define event identity, cursor generation, retention windows, replay ordering, and how durable journal state relates to runtime projections and source health. The implementation should make cursor expiration and resync explicit instead of leaving them as accidental behavior.\\n\\nThis task should also preserve the existing attention-feed intent while upgrading its durability and transport neutrality.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when ntm can append and replay durable attention events from SQLite with stable ordering and explicit cursor semantics that later digest/attention/transport tasks can rely on.","notes":"Treat the cursor model as contract-critical. If it is vague, every delta consumer becomes brittle.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":240,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:28.716724326Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T16:37:19.968369465Z","closed_at":"2026-03-22T16:37:19.967884354Z","close_reason":"Verified already implemented. AttentionStore interface (attention_feed.go:21-34) with AppendAttentionEvent, GetAttentionEventsSince, GetAttentionReplayWindow, GetLatestEventCursor, GCExpiredEvents. SQLite implementation (runtime_store.go:1024-1163) with INSERT INTO attention_events, cursor model, replay window queries, GC. CursorAllocator for monotonic cursors. AttentionFeedConfig with JournalSize, RetentionPeriod, HeartbeatInterval.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["attention","events","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:52.457652326Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:52.932305610Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:53.418895657Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:28.716724326Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":325,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.1","author":"ubuntu","text":"Future self: this task is where the current good attention-feed direction becomes restart-safe infrastructure instead of a clever in-memory convenience.","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:29Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.4.2","title":"robot-redesign/attention: publish durable events from adapters and monitors","description":"Emit durable attention events from the normalized adapters and monitoring logic instead of synthesizing them only in ad hoc surface code. This task exists because the durable journal only matters if source changes and operator-significant events are published consistently at the right seam.","design":"The publication model should define which normalized changes become events, which categories and reason codes they carry, how duplicate/noisy events are suppressed, and which events remain background versus action-required.\\n\\nThis is where we make event production systematic rather than letting each renderer invent its own idea of what changed.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when major normalized sources can publish durable attention events with stable categories, reason codes, and actionability semantics into the SQLite journal.","notes":"If event meaning still depends on where you read it from, this task is incomplete.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:29.989067017Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T23:28:16.404296449Z","closed_at":"2026-03-22T23:28:16.403776386Z","close_reason":"Normalized adapters already published durable attention; PT monitor callbacks now bridge into the durable attention journal with stable PT reason codes, actionability, dedup windows, and repo-wide verification (go build ./cmd/ntm, go test -short ./..., golangci-lint run).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["attention","publish","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:56.756502539Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:57.236294556Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:39:57.715435965Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:29.989067017Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.2","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:38.473709208Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.4.3","title":"robot-redesign/attention: persist output/activity watermarks for restart-safe deltas","description":"Persist the output and activity baselines needed to compute deltas across restarts and refresh boundaries. This task exists because output-derived activity and stall semantics are much less trustworthy if they reset whenever ntm itself restarts.","design":"The design should specify what is persisted per pane/agent, how hash or line-count baselines are maintained, how buffer wrap/reset is handled, and how those baselines feed both runtime projections and event publication.\\n\\nThis task should also make explicit which baselines are durable versus ephemeral cache-only accelerators.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when output/activity delta computation can survive ntm process restarts without collapsing into unknown state or spurious activity transitions.","notes":"The purpose is restart-safe semantics, not perfect eternal scrollback knowledge. Persist only what materially improves delta correctness.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:30.840575487Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T18:51:37.404726408Z","closed_at":"2026-03-22T18:51:37.404062634Z","close_reason":"Implemented restart-safe output/activity baselines: WatermarkStore interface, WithWatermarkStore option, first-sample baseline (charsAdded=0), post-restart hash-match (uses stored rune count), post-restart hash-mismatch (buffer reset, charsAdded=0), velocity=0 across restart boundary. 11 focused tests pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["attention","robot-redesign","watermarks"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:30.840575487Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:38.896111706Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","title":"robot-redesign/attention: align replay, resync, and degraded semantics across transports","description":"Make sure CLI replay, REST replay, SSE streams, and WebSocket event delivery all share the same cursor, resync, and degraded-state semantics. This task exists because transport-specific drift would undermine trust in the operator loop even if the core event store is correct.","design":"The work should describe and implement how cursor expiry, replay windows, degraded event publication, deduplicated or suppressed item semantics, resurfacing after cooldown, operator acknowledgment or snooze state, pin or escalation state, request-correlation or retry semantics, resync hints, and recoverable error semantics appear across transports. Consumers should be able to switch transport without re-learning what a cursor means, how a degraded source is reported, how an aggregated or snoozed attention item behaves, or how to recover from a stale, duplicated, or unsupported request. This task makes the event-store contract portable rather than CLI-only.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when replay, resync, degraded-state, aggregation, operator-attention-state, and request-correlation behavior are semantically aligned across all supported transports and documented strongly enough for parity tests to pin them down.","notes":"Transport parity belongs here because replay semantics are part of the event product, not just a server detail.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:31.737490476Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T00:49:01.313595549Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["attention","parity","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.12","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:47:57.234625942Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:02:32.670554852Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:31.737490476Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:39.331779235Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:39.750886162Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:40.187026276Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:18:02.606202998Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:42.362200462Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:30:01.899173486Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":334,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Watch-semantics follow-up: transport alignment explicitly includes heartbeat cadence, replay-to-live transition markers, filtered subscription behavior, unsupported-selector handling, and the distinction between durable material events and ephemeral keepalives.","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:49:01Z"}]}
-{"id":"bd-j9jo3.4.5","title":"robot-redesign/attention: publish actuation outcomes and closed-loop verification events","description":"Publish durable actuation-outcome and reconciliation events so the operator loop becomes closed-loop rather than hopeful. This task exists because once ntm points agents toward existing control commands, the system also needs a first-class way to tell them whether a request started, succeeded, partially applied, timed out, was superseded, or still needs verification.","design":"The work should define how existing robot control commands emit or correlate durable events representing request receipt, request or correlation ID and idempotency semantics where applicable, target reference, expected effect, observed effect, timeout or supersession, and final verification state. It should distinguish direct command execution results from later observed convergence in runtime state, define pending versus confirmed versus failed versus unknown outcomes, and explain how these outcome events appear in digest, attention, diagnostics, and parity transports. This task should improve operator confidence without inventing hidden planner behavior. The system already has explicit actuation commands; the missing piece is trustworthy feedback and reconciliation.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when the attention journal and related surfaces can represent actuation requests plus later outcome or reconciliation evidence strongly enough that consumers know whether to proceed, wait, retry, inspect, or escalate, and can correlate that evidence back to the originating request without guesswork. The result must make write-loop verification a first-class part of the operator story rather than a side effect inferred from unrelated state diffs.","notes":"If an agent still has to grep output or manually diff snapshots to decide whether its own command actually worked, this task is incomplete.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-22T00:15:58.089840762Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:28.241055679Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["attention","events","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:31.247574320Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:17:58.777177886Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:17:59.409702056Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:18:00.040649585Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:28.240300324Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:15:58.089840762Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:18:00.642678033Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:18:01.284467413Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.5","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:18:01.916828888Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","title":"robot-redesign/attention: implement deduplication, aggregation, cooldown, and saturation policies","description":"Implement the attention-hygiene layer that turns durable events into an operator-usable queue instead of a stream of repetitive churn. This task exists because even a correct durable journal will feel hostile if repeated source flaps, restarts, unread-mail bursts, or ongoing degraded states spam digest and attention with near-duplicate items.","design":"The work should define and implement how repeated events are deduplicated or rolled up, how cooldown and resurfacing windows work, how persistent conditions escalate from repeated attention items into incidents, how actuation-outcome events and diagnostic evidence are merged into existing items, how operator acknowledgment, snooze, mute, and pin state interact with automatic ranking, and how bounded attention budgets prefer the most decision-relevant items without hiding important recurrence. It should make suppression, aggregation, and operator overrides explainable rather than silent so operators can still tell why an item appeared once, changed severity, stayed hidden, or re-emerged after cooldown or snooze expiry. This is not about hiding bad news. It is about preserving signal-to-noise and operator trust.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when attention and digest can present a concise, prioritized queue that resists duplicate churn, surfaces recurrence intentionally, and makes suppression, aggregation, and operator override rules inspectable.","notes":"If a transient flapping source can drown out real action items or if repeated retries create visually separate clutter instead of a coherent thread, this task is incomplete.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-22T00:22:30.983883067Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T00:31:41.855072800Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["attention","ergonomics","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:47.677398631Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:39.372257751Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:39.923451425Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:22:30.983883067Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:40.492417876Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:41.098650417Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:41.701904070Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-j9jo3.4.7","title":"robot-redesign/attention: persist operator attention state and re-emergence rules","description":"Implement the durable operator-attention state that lets users and agents intentionally shape the queue over time. This task exists because the redesign should not force consumers to passively accept automatic ranking forever; they need durable semantics for acknowledged, snoozed, muted, pinned, and manually escalated items so the attention loop becomes collaborative rather than naggy.","design":"The implementation should persist operator attention state in SQLite, keyed strongly enough to survive restarts and correlate with stable item identities or incident fingerprints rather than brittle presentation text. It should define how acknowledged, snoozed, muted, pinned, and manually escalated items influence ranking, visibility, resurfacing, and incident promotion; how manual state interacts with automatic deduplication and cooldown; what happens when an item changes materially while snoozed or acknowledged; and how expired snoozes or changed conditions reintroduce items into digest and attention. It should also expose enough evidence that diagnostics and parity surfaces can explain why an item was hidden, resurfaced, pinned, or force-escalated. This task is where the attention loop becomes collaborative rather than one-way.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when operator attention state is durably persisted and the system can consistently honor acknowledgment, snooze, mute, pin, and manual escalation semantics across restart, replay, resurfacing, and prioritization behavior.","notes":"If users still have no durable way to say not now, keep this visible, or this matters more than the default ranking thinks, this task is incomplete.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:01.332214259Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T00:30:01.238815078Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["attention","ergonomics","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:58.204176406Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.2.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:58.782560632Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:01.332214259Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:59.373249588Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:30:00.001006793Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:30:00.658481031Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.7","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.5.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:30:01.238264417Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-j9jo3.4.8","title":"robot-redesign/attention: implement watch subscriptions, heartbeats, and adaptive cadence semantics","description":"Implement the long-lived watch semantics that make ntm's event loop safe and pleasant to consume over time: typed event publication, heartbeats, filtered subscriptions, idle-vs-stuck liveness, and adaptive cadence. This task exists because the current redesign is strong on durable replay and operator prioritization, but it still leaves too much ambiguity around what continuous consumers should see when nothing material changes, when sources are slow, or when a consumer only wants a narrow slice of the event stream.","design":"The implementation should define and build how the durable attention journal, transport layer, and source-health logic cooperate to emit typed watch events and explicit keepalive behavior without flooding the system with meaningless churn. It should decide which signals are durably persisted versus emitted only as ephemeral transport keepalives, how heartbeat cadence and liveness deadlines are derived, how filtered subscriptions are evaluated against stable references and event classes, how replay hands off cleanly to live updates, and how source-progress or projection-status annotations tell consumers whether quiet means healthy idle, narrow filtering, temporary source slowness, or a real stuck condition.\n\nThis work should also implement adaptive cadence or similar pressure control so high-churn periods stay responsive while low-churn or degraded periods remain operationally cheap. The goal is not a complex scheduler. The goal is to keep long-lived watch consumers trustworthy, bounded, and intelligible. The implementation should reuse existing cursor, identity, explainability, request-correlation, source-health, and boundedness semantics rather than inventing a parallel model just for streaming.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when ntm can support long-lived filtered watch or streaming consumption with explicit typed events, trustworthy heartbeats, clear idle-vs-stuck semantics, replay-to-live handoff, and adaptive cadence behavior that stays aligned with the shared attention and transport contracts.","notes":"If a future agent still has to guess whether a quiet stream is healthy, filtered down, lagging, or silently broken, this task is incomplete.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":210,"created_at":"2026-03-22T00:47:02.724224253Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:07.707520510Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["attention","robot-redesign","streaming"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.12","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:03.695584425Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.3.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:07.706799550Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:47:02.724224253Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:06.923200325Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:06.156707440Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:05.389480671Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.8","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:04.526063040Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","title":"robot-redesign/attention: align replay, resync, and degraded semantics across transports","description":"Make sure CLI replay, REST replay, SSE streams, and WebSocket event delivery all share the same cursor, resync, and degraded-state semantics. This task exists because transport-specific drift would undermine trust in the operator loop even if the core event store is correct.","design":"The work should describe and implement how cursor expiry, replay windows, degraded event publication, deduplicated or suppressed item semantics, resurfacing after cooldown, operator acknowledgment or snooze state, pin or escalation state, request-correlation or retry semantics, resync hints, and recoverable error semantics appear across transports. Consumers should be able to switch transport without re-learning what a cursor means, how a degraded source is reported, how an aggregated or snoozed attention item behaves, or how to recover from a stale, duplicated, or unsupported request. This task makes the event-store contract portable rather than CLI-only.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when replay, resync, degraded-state, aggregation, operator-attention-state, and request-correlation behavior are semantically aligned across all supported transports and documented strongly enough for parity tests to pin them down.","notes":"Operator loop moved here after closing bd-j9jo3.4.7. Starting bounded parity pass across CLI/REST/SSE/WebSocket replay-resync-degraded semantics.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:31.737490476Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T04:56:58.847838491Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T04:56:58.847379973Z","close_reason":"Aligned attention replay cursor-expired semantics across REST/SSE with the robot contract by replacing legacy resync_hint payloads with machine-readable resync_command sourced from CursorExpiredDetails; focused serve tests, go build ./cmd/ntm, go test -short ./..., golangci-lint run, and touched-file format/import checks are green.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["attention","parity","robot-redesign"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.12","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:47:57.234625942Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:02:32.670554852Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:31.737490476Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:39.331779235Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:39.750886162Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:34:40.187026276Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:18:02.606202998Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:42.362200462Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:30:01.899173486Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":334,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.4.4","author":"ubuntu","text":"Watch-semantics follow-up: transport alignment explicitly includes heartbeat cadence, replay-to-live transition markers, filtered subscription behavior, unsupported-selector handling, and the distinction between durable material events and ephemeral keepalives.","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:49:01Z"}]}
+{"id":"bd-j9jo3.4.5","title":"robot-redesign/attention: publish actuation outcomes and closed-loop verification events","description":"Publish durable actuation-outcome and reconciliation events so the operator loop becomes closed-loop rather than hopeful. This task exists because once ntm points agents toward existing control commands, the system also needs a first-class way to tell them whether a request started, succeeded, partially applied, timed out, was superseded, or still needs verification.","design":"The work should define how existing robot control commands emit or correlate durable events representing request receipt, request or correlation ID and idempotency semantics where applicable, target reference, expected effect, observed effect, timeout or supersession, and final verification state. It should distinguish direct command execution results from later observed convergence in runtime state, define pending versus confirmed versus failed versus unknown outcomes, and explain how these outcome events appear in digest, attention, diagnostics, and parity transports. This task should improve operator confidence without inventing hidden planner behavior. The system already has explicit actuation commands; the missing piece is trustworthy feedback and reconciliation.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when the attention journal and related surfaces can represent actuation requests plus later outcome or reconciliation evidence strongly enough that consumers know whether to proceed, wait, retry, inspect, or escalate, and can correlate that evidence back to the originating request without guesswork. The result must make write-loop verification a first-class part of the operator story rather than a side effect inferred from unrelated state diffs.","notes":"If an agent still has to grep output or manually diff snapshots to decide whether its own command actually worked, this task is incomplete.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estim